If Ludo be read, it may be either from the Latin ludus (Naevius entitled a comedy Ludius) or from Λυδός, Lydian. —- poetae: Naevius seems to have been in the habit of adding poeta to his name. It appears in the well-known epitaph said to have been written by himself, also in the lines written against him by the family poet of the Metelli: ‘ malum dabunt Metelli Naevio poetae '.
